noun.description: An eyelet placed in a hole in a sheet or panel to protect or insulate a rope or cable passed through it or to prevent the sheet or panel from being torn.
A tube surgically implanted in the eardrum to drain fluid from the middle ear.
A young or inexperienced skier, snowboarder, surfer, or skateboarder.
examples: mega moves that make gods out of grommets

origin: Early 17th century (in nautical use in the sense a circle of rope used as a fastening): from obsolete French grommette, from gourmer to curb, of unknown ultimate origin. Current senses date from the mid 20th century.
